    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-20T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-20T05:00:00-05:00" n="831"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d831">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/1686</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-20T10:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 20, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.19 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2113. War Trade Board [from <persName>Rickard</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>]:</p>
                <p>392. Refer to Embassy’s 1761, August 31, 7 p.m., [our] 233, and Department’s
                    1535, September 9, 4 p.m., your 240. We have not <pb facs="0912" n="1746"
                        xml:id="pg_1746"/> been informed of results of Cuban negotiations. Consul at
                    Corunna informs us most boats plying directly between Cuba and his port carry
                    bunker forms and licenses from War Trade Board representative at Habana. Please
                    advise us: (1) if War Trade Board representative at Habana has authority to
                    issue bunker [licenses for] boats plying directly between Spain and Cuba and not
                    touching a port of United States or its possessions; (2) if so, what is source
                    of his authority? Rickard. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1"
                        >Chadbourne</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
